  "prompt": "How do I remove a non-friend from Facebook messenger contact list?",
  "response": "To remove a non-friend from your Facebook Messenger contact list, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Block the Person:**\n   - Open the Messenger app on your device.\n   - Find the conversation with the person you want to remove.\n   - Tap on their name or the profile picture at the top of the chat.\n   - Scroll down and select \"Block.\"\n   - Confirm your choice by selecting \"Block on Messenger.\"\n\n2. **Delete the Conversation:**\n   - In Messenger, navigate to the chat you want to delete.\n   - Swipe left (iOS) or tap and hold (Android) on the conversation.\n   - Choose \"Delete.\"\n   - Confirm the deletion if prompted.\n\nBlocking the person will prevent them from messaging you again and effectively remove them from your Messenger contact list. Deleting the conversation is an additional step to clear it from your chat history. Note that blocking someone on Messenger does not unfriend them on Facebook, if they are a friend, but it will prevent them from contacting you via Messenger.",
